Save £1,000+ in a day
A crash course in how to give yourself a money makeover ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/family/money-help )

The savings from examining if you can save on every element of
your finances can be huge. There are two ways to do it, and it's
January so let's give it a go.

- A financial blitz: Take a day and treat it like a job, or a
day's work. Many can save £1,000+/yr doing this. And if so, then
unless you earn £470,000+ pre-tax (see our income tax calc ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/tax-calculator/ )), it'll be
your best paid day of the year.

- A slow burn: Here you do the big and easy stuff now, then
through the year each time you get a bill, try and cut it. I of
course prefer the blitz - here's how.

07:45. While singing in the shower, ask the 'water bills'
question. Save up to £500. Live in Eng or Wales? Ask: "Does my
home have more or the same no of bedrooms as people?" If yes,
it's likely you'll save by fitting a water meter. So use a water
bills calculator ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/utilities/cut-water-bills#calculators ). As Andy emailed us: "Before water meter = £54 a month x 10
months. After water meter = £48 a quarter, £348 saved a year."

( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/family/money-help )08:00.
Energy call centres open now - check if your OLD supplier owes
you cash. Reclaim up to £600. If you've switched energy in the
last five years your old provider may still owe you credit, as
many operated a 'don't ask, don't get' policy.

So call them up and ask - full help & numbers in Reclaim Old
Energy Credit ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/utilities/reclaim-energy-bill-refunds ). As Sarah emailed us: "I switched energy to a new provider and
assumed my account with the old provider would be closed and
settled. It hadn't and after reading the MSE email I chased and
got back £697."

08:15. Check if you'll be accepted for a 0debt costs. Save up to £1,000. Now you're awake enough, let's do
a big and easy one. If you've got debts on a credit card, use
our 0you shift your credit card debts to them to slash costs. (New to
balance transfers? Watch Martin's ITV show ( https://www.itv.com/itvplayer/the-martin-lewis-money-show ) from
last Friday for a run-through.)

Top pick 0
Find the card you're most likely to get with our
ELIGIBILITY CALC ( http://www.msetool.co.uk/redirect/credit_cardeligibility?url=https://creditcards.moneysavingexpert.com/?balance-transfer )

See the latest tip: http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/tips/21-01-15

Full info and more options in Best Balance Transfers ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/balance-transfer-credit-cards ) (APR examples ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/credit-card-apr-examples )) - and if you are doing this, always follow the golden rules...

a) Repay at least the set monthly min, or you can lose special
rates.

b) Always clear the card or shift again before the 0rates jump.

c) Don't spend/withdraw cash on them. That's not at the cheap
rate.

d) Unsure what to pick? Use our Which Card Is Cheapest? ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/balance-transfer-credit-cards#tool ) tool.

08:30. Are you dressed yet? Do you (did you) wear a uniform?
Reclaim up to £300. OK, get out of those PJs. If you wear (or
wore) a uniform to work, and wash it yourself, you may be due a
lower tax bill. As forumite Jinx80 wrote: "I rang the tax office
and I'm getting a £60/year rebate for the last 4 years. Really
chuffed." Full help & templates: Uniform Tax Rebates ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/reclaim/uniform-tax-rebate ).

09:00. Save £230+ on your energy bills in 310 seconds. We're
giving this 15 minutes, but it should be far quicker. We used a
stopwatch to time four newbies to the MSE Towers team using
the Cheap Energy Club ( http://www.msetool.co.uk/redirect/energy_toppicks ) - the
quickest took 202s, the longest 376s. The avg was 310s with a
£226 saving. See Don't let BG price cuts fool you ( #energy )
info below for the latest deals.

09:15. Prepared to get serious? Give yourself a financial
assessment. Switch off Jeremy Kyle (though turn it back on for
This Morning, I may be on). It's time to find out if you spend
more than you earn.

To do this, gather your bank & credit card statements, and plug
your finances into our Budget Analyser ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/banking/Budget-planning ). It'll
take you through how to check everything and see if you've
overspent. To inspire you: Watch others 'press the button' ( http://www.itv.com/goodmorningbritain/money/martin-lewis-money-diet-its-weigh-in-time ).

11:00. Time for a free tea or coffee. Get a daily free Waitrose
tea or coffee. ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/waitrose#deal26402 )

11:15. Hit the phone to haggle broadband, digital TV, breakdown
cover. Companies often raise prices each year hoping you'll do
nowt. If you like the service and don't want to switch, the
alternative is to haggle - this is best done near your contract's
end.

The powerhouse trick is to threaten to leave so you get put
through to disconnections, known internally as 'customer
retentions', as its job is to keep you. In our recent poll, 86of Sky and 84help see our How to Haggle ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/phones/negotiate-with-service-providers ) guide.

Dave emailed us: "My Sky renewal price went from £60 to £94. I
followed your haggling tips and got the same package for £405
less."

12:15. Spend a penny. It's been more than an hour since that free
tea and coffee. If you think there's no way to save here, see
cutting loo paper use ( http://forums.moneysavingexpert.com/showthread.php?p=55635407 ).

12:20. Check if you're being ripped off on car insurance. Save up
to £1,000. Price hikes are predicted, so everyone should check
now. If you're not at renewal, and can make big savings, provided
you've not claimed you can oft get a full rebate on your existing
policy for a c.£50 admin fee.

Our Cheap Car Insurance ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/ ) guide has full
help. Yet at speed... combine comparison sites to get a wide
spread - our current order's: 1) MoneySup* ( http://www.moneysupermarket.com/car-insurance/?Source=MSE ) 2)
Confused* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/4fb28432 ) 3)
CompMarket ( http://www.comparethemarket.com/car-insurance/ ) -
then check Direct Line* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/70fd449b ), Aviva* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/40185edc )and Zurich ( http://www.zurich.co.uk/car/ ) that they miss, plus Admiral
Multicar* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/38865c73 ) if
you've more than one car in the home.

As Becky emailed us: "My renewal cost was £895.89 but I managed
to get another deal for £357. That's a saving of about £538. I am
very grateful."

There are a host of other tricks to slash prices too. See Cheap
Car Insurance ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/ )
& Cheap Young Drivers' Insurance ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/young-drivers )
for more.

13:00. Lunchtime - gnaw down your food bills. Save £1,000+.
Rummage through your fridge, cupboards or even larder to check
how many top-end or manufacturers' brands there are. Lots? The
Downshift Challenge Tool ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/downshift-challenge/ )
could chop £850 a year off a £100 weekly shop. Plus see 30 Food
Shopping Tricks ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/cheap-supermarket-shopping ). Once finished, grab some lunch and take a breather.

14:00 Overpaying on your mortgage? Save £1,000s. Mortgage rates
are plummeting and fixed-rate mortgages are still at or close to
historic lows, but there's concern they'll rise soon. Everyone
should check their rate now and see what's out there. Here's
where to get the info.

1) Free MSE Remortgage Guide: Instant PDF ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/mortgages/remortgage-guide?form=pdf#form ) | Order Printed ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/mortgages/remortgage-guide?form=printed#form ).

2) Benchmark top rates with the MSE Mortgage Best Buys ( http://www.msetool.co.uk/redirect/mortgages_bestbuy?url=http://mse.me/remortbestbuys ) tool.

Sarah emailed us: "I saved £500/mth by remortgaging to a new
5-year fix, saving £30k in 5 years. It took time, but the effort
paid off."

14:45. Are you due £1,000s back? Time for a reclaim sesh. Save
£100 - £20,000. Many people have unknowingly had money taken
from them. Never assume "it's not me"...

1) Check your tax code. If you're an employee or pensioner, your
tax code dictates what tax you pay and millions are wrong. Use
our free Tax Code Calc ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/family/check-tax-code ) to
check. As Nina found: "I checked and found the taxman owed me
£1,300 and I'll be £160 a month better off. Thank you."

2) Got or had a loan, credit or store card, etc? Many had PPI
added even if they said no. There are billions more to be paid
out. See our Reclaim PPI for Free ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/reclaim/ppi-loan-insurance )
guide. As Barry emailed: "I followed your advice, used the
template and just received a cheque for £17,900."

3) Had bank charges when in financial hardship? If you had
charges for going beyond your limit you may be able to reclaim
bank charges. ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/reclaim/bank-charges ) As Rick
tweeted us: "I followed your advice re bank charges for my
brother who lost his job - he got £252 paid into his account.
Thank you."

4) Pay (or paid) a monthly fee for your bank account? Many people
were sold extras that weren't valid, see if you can reclaim bank
fees ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/reclaim/reclaim-packaged-bank-accounts ). As Cheryl tweeted us: "Had nearly £3,000 in packaged bank
account fees refunded this morning thanks to @MartinSLewis ( https://twitter.com/MartinSLewis ) and @MoneySavingExp ( https://twitter.com/MoneySavingExp )."

5) Had a flight delay of more than 3hrs in the last 6 years? This
one isn't a reclaim, it's a fixed amount of compensation. See our
Flight Delays/Cancellation ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/travel/flight-delays ) guide. As
Eilidh emailed us: "I was delayed for 4 hours in St Lucia. I
followed your step-by-step guide and used your helpful templates
and within 2 months we were given €1,200 compensation."

15:45. The school run - beware potholes. Save £100s. If your car
or bike's been crocked by a pothole, you can try to claim the
repair cost from the authority responsible. See Pothole Claims ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/travel/pothole-claims ).

16:15. Free £125 (or 3account. Save £100s. Switching your current account takes just 7
working days - all direct debits & standing orders are moved for
you and payments to your old account are auto-forwarded. Full
info in Best Bank Accounts ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/banking/compare-best-bank-accounts ).

- Free £125 & top customer service: 92Direct* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/a064232a ) as
great and it currently pays new switchers £125 (normally £100).
It also has a linked 6to qualify (for most it just means pay salary in).

- Up to 3( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/redir/4d519365 ) pays 3if you've £3k-£20k in it. There's a £2/mth fee but for many
that's covered by the 1on Facebook: "I've had the Santander 123 account for nearly 18
months and even with the £2 per month I've got nearly £900 in
interest and cashback."

16:45. Grab a diary and fill it in - don't pay the lazy tax. This
is perhaps the most important thing you'll do today. Grab your
diary & go through all products with timed elements - eg, car
insurance renewal, 0more. Put a note in a month before each one ends to ditch &
switch.

17:15. Hungry for more? These are just a selection of things to
do. See 40+ Money Makeover Tips ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/family/money-help ) and Stop
Spending ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/family/stop-spending-budgeting-tool ) guides.

17:30. If you've finished, spread the savings word. I put all the
new ways to save and new deals in this email. If you read it each
week, you should never be overspending. So why not take five
minutes to suggest to friends and family they get it too? They
can sign up to the free weekly email ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/site/money-tips-email-faqs )
here.

20:00. No one to go out with? Try free online dating. Save £100s.
January is the busiest time of year for online dating, yet it
can be tough to sort the good from the bad, ugly and downright
strange.

Try out the top MoneySaving dating sites in our online dating ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/free-dating-sites )
guide.

PS. New. The Martin Lewis Money Roadshow, ITV1, Fri 8pm - flight
delays, ISAs, energy & power of attorney. This week it's all
about the latest flight delays info plus ISA tips, energy price
cuts, and how to protect your family if you lose your faculties.
Watch last week's ( https://www.itv.com/itvplayer/the-martin-lewis-money-show )
credit card cost-cutting special.

