     <a name="mands" id="mands" style="color: #0047d9;"></a><a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/best-0-credit-cards?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=bignote-two&amp;utm_term=21-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=credit-cards&amp;utm_content=1" class="headline" style="color: #0047d9; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 20px; text-decoration: none;">Free &pound;30 M&amp;S voucher with top 19mth 0     <span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; color: #222; font-weight: bold;">It's a  top card if you <em>need</em> to borrow. If not, just buy an apple to get the voucher, which is valid for  food &amp; wine</span></a>
      <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 22px;">Sign up for a credit card, get accepted, spend a penny and it gives  a freebie - booyakasha - then forget it. Or, if you need to borrow it's a decent 0      <ul>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0;"><a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/best-0-credit-cards?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=bignote-two&amp;utm_term=21-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=credit-cards&amp;utm_content=2" style="color: #0047d9;"><img src="http://images.moneysavingexpert.com/images/mandsvoucher2.gif" alt="M&amp;S voucher" width="165" height="150" border="0" align="right" style="outline: none; text-decoration: none; -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none;" /></a> <strong>New. 19mth 0          <em><br />
          - Free voucher &amp; M&amp;S points. </em>Spend just 1p or more by 31 March  and you'll be emailed a &pound;30 M&amp;S food voucher (no min spend)   by 30 April, valid till 31 May on food, wine  and flowers - so  if you don't need it to borrow with, just make the spend and pay it off. Also you earn 1 M&amp;S point, worth a penny in stores, per &pound;1 spent in M&amp;S,  and per &pound;2  elsewhere. <br />
          <br />
       <em>- How good is the 0        </li>
       <li style="margin-bottom: 22px; margin-left: 0;"><strong>0          <br />
        </strong>a) Always plan what you need to borrow (be careful), minimise it and ensure you can cover  repayments. <br />
        b) Pay at least the monthly min and keep within your credit limit, or you risk losing the 0        c)  Don't just apply in hope, that marks your credit file. Use our <a href="http://www.msetool.co.uk/redirect/credit_cardeligibility?url=https://creditcards.moneysavingexpert.com/?purchases" target="_blank" style="color: #0047d9;">0        d) Aim to clear the card (or at least  <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/credit-cards/balance-transfer-credit-cards?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=bignote-two&amp;utm_term=21-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=credit-cards&amp;utm_content=8" style="color: #0047d9;"> balance transfer</a> it) before the 0          e) Don't  withdraw cash - it's not usually at the cheap rate and can hit your <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/loans/credit-rating-credit-score?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=bignote-two&amp;utm_term=21-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=loans&amp;utm_content=9" style="color: #0047d9;">credit score</a>.
